<activity xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xml:id="act-8a-1-2">
	<statement>
		<p>
			Let <m>f(x)=e^x</m> and <m>T(x) = k_0 + k_1 x + k_2 x^2 + k_3 x^3</m>.  
		</p>
		<p>
			<ol marker="a.">
				<li>
					<p>
						By computing the second and third derivatives of <m>T(x)</m> and evaluating <m>T</m> and its derivatives at <m>a = 0</m>, fill in the blank entries in <xref ref="T-act-8a-1-2">Table</xref>.

						<table xml:id="T-act-8a-1-2">
						<title>Formulas and values for <m>f(x)</m> and <m>T(x)</m>.</title>
							<tabular top="minor" bottom="minor">
								<row>
									<cell halign="right"><m>f(x)=</m></cell>
									<cell><m>e^x</m></cell>
									<cell halign="right"><m>T(x)=</m></cell>
									<cell><m>k_0 + k_1 x + k_2 x^2 + k_3 x^3</m></cell>
								</row>
								<row>
									<cell halign="right"><m>f'(x)=</m></cell>
									<cell><m>e^x</m></cell>
									<cell halign="right"><m>T'(x)=</m></cell>
									<cell><m>k_1 + 2 k_2 x + 3 k_3 x^2</m></cell>
								</row>                
								<row>
									<cell halign="right"><m>f''(x)=</m></cell>
									<cell><m>e^x</m></cell>
									<cell halign="right"><m>T''(x)=</m></cell>
									<cell><fillin /></cell>
								</row>
								<row>
									<cell halign="right"><m>f'''(x)=</m></cell>
									<cell><m>e^x</m></cell>
									<cell halign="right"><m>T'''(x)=</m></cell>
									<cell><fillin /></cell>
								</row>

								<row>
									<cell></cell>
									<cell></cell>
									<cell></cell>
									<cell></cell>
								</row>
								<row>
									<cell halign="right"><m>f(0)=</m></cell>
									<cell><m>1</m></cell>
									<cell halign="right"><m>T(0)=</m></cell>
									<cell><m>k_0</m></cell>
								</row>
								<row>
									<cell halign="right"><m>f'(0)=</m></cell>
									<cell><m>1</m></cell>
									<cell halign="right"><m>T'(0)=</m></cell>
									<cell><m>k_1</m></cell>
								</row>                
								<row>
									<cell halign="right"><m>f''(0)=</m></cell>
									<cell><m>1</m></cell>
									<cell halign="right"><m>T''(0)=</m></cell>
									<cell><fillin /></cell>
								</row>
								<row>
									<cell halign="right"><m>f'''(0)=</m></cell>
									<cell><m>1</m></cell>
									<cell halign="right"><m>T'''(0)=</m></cell>
									<cell><fillin /></cell>
								</row>
							</tabular>
						</table>
					</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<p>
						Next, recall that we want <m>f</m> and <m>T</m> to share the same function and derivative values at <m>a = 0</m> up to and including the third derivative.  For instance, one of the four needed equations is <m>T’(0) = f’(0)</m>.  What does our work in <xref ref="T-act-8a-1-2">Table</xref> tell us about the values of <m>k_0</m>, <m>k_1</m>, <m>k_2</m>, and <m>k_3</m>?

					</p>
				</li>
				<li>
					<p>
						Having now determined the numerical values of <m>k_0</m>, <m>k_1</m>, <m>k_2</m>, and <m>k_3</m>, plot the function <m>T(x) = k_0 + k_1 x + k_2 x^2 + k_3 x^3</m> along with <m>f(x)=e^x</m>, <m>L(x)=1+x</m>, and <m>Q(x) = 1 + x + \frac{1}{2}x^2</m> in <xref ref="F-8a-1-act-2">Figure</xref>.  What do you notice?  For about which values of <m>x</m> is <m>|f(x)-T(x)| \lt 0.1</m>?

						<figure xml:id="F-8a-1-act-2">
							<caption>The function <m>f(x)=e^x</m>, its tangent line <m>L(x)=1+x</m>, and the quadratic approximation <m>Q(x) = 1 + x + \frac{1}{2}x^2</m> near the point <m>(0,f(0))</m>.</caption>
							<image width="50%" source="images/8a_1_act_2" />
						</figure>
					</p>		
				</li>
				<li>
					<p>
						What if we wanted a fourth degree polynomial approximation to <m>f(x) = e^x</m> near <m>a = 0</m>?  Based on the patterns you’ve observed in <m>L</m>, <m>Q</m>, and <m>T</m>, conjecture values for the constants <m>w_0, \ldots, w_4</m> for a function <m>S</m> of the form
						<me>S(x) = w_0 + w_1 x + w_2 x^2 + w_3 x^3 + w_3 x^4</me>
						that satisfies <m>S(0) = f(0)</m>, <m>S'(0) = f'(0)</m>, <m>\ldots</m>, <m>S^{(4)}(0) = f^{(4)}(0)</m>.  Add this function <m>S</m> to your earlier work in <xref ref="F-8a-1-act-2">Figure</xref>.  What do you notice?
					</p>
				</li>
			</ol>
		</p>
		</statement>
